vities and the associated costs are also fully discussed. With many worked examples throughout the text, this will be an essential book for anyone either preparing or assessing a disruption and loss of productivity claims, including architects, contract administrators, project managers and quantity surveyors as well as contractors, contracts consultants and construction lawyers"--cProvided by publisher.  aDescription based on print version record and CIP data provided by publisher; resource not viewed.  a44 0aConstruction contractszGreat Britain.403University of Alberta Accessuhttp://dx.doi.org/10.1002/9781118992159z(Unlimited Concurrent Users)  hUAINzWILEYOL  aInternet AccesswLCc1i6855787-1001lINTERNETmUAINTERNETrYsYtE-RESOURCEu3/9/2015xE-BOOKzWILEYOL01ahttp://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/n2007070823bhttp://viaf.org/viaf/68386199